%global pkg_name linux-file-extents

Name:           %{pkg_name}
Version:        0.2.0.0
Release:        0
Summary:        Retrieve file fragmentation information under Linux
Group:          Development/Libraries/Haskell

License:        BSD-3-Clause
Url:            https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}
Source0:        https://hackage.haskell.org/package/%{name}-%{version}/%{name}-%{version}.tar.gz

BuildRequires:  ghc-Cabal-devel
BuildRequires:  ghc-rpm-macros
BuildRequires:  ghc-unix-devel

%description
This package provides a simple wrapper around the Linux FIEMAP ioctl.
It can be used to retrieve the list of all the extents of any given file, i.e.
the area of the disk where the file is actually stored. This is similar to the
'filefrag' command line tool provided by the 'e2fsprogs' package.


